frameDefinitions: A Visitor arrives at the Host_location as a guest of the Host, for the purpose of achieving a Purpose.
The Authorities hold a Suspect under suspicion of having committed a crime (Charges).
A Patient is committed to the care of a medical Facility by a proper Authority.
A Speaker addresses an Audience on a particular Topic.
An object Theme moves in the direction of a Goal.
frameExamples: I'm gonna <t>drop</t> <t>in</t> on Kieth for a while.
The police <t>held</t> Mr. Smith in the slammer on charges of killing his lawyer.
Ten years after Abraham Lincoln's assassination, a Chicago court declared his 56-year-old widow Mary insane and <t>committed</t> her to a mental institution.
McNamara <t>addressed</t> congress on the state of affairs of the Department of Defense.
Some students <t>arrived</t> at the school on Sunday.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Visitor</fen> arrives at the Host_location to visit the <fen>Host</fen> for a <fen>Purpose</fen>.

The <fen>Host</fen> is the person highly associated with the goal location of the <fen>Visitor</fen>, and who allows the <fen>Visitor</fen> onto his/her territory, and possibly to make use of available resources. The <fen>Host</fen> and <fen>Visitor</fen> and in a host-guest relationship.
The <fen>Host_location</fen> is a place primarily associated with the <fen>Host</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when arriving occurs.
The larger area within which the visiting takes place.
The <fen>Authorities</fen> hold the <fen>Suspect</fen> in custody.
This role identifies the person who is taken into custody and held, under suspicion of having committed a crime.
When the detaining occurs.
Where the detaining takes place.
The person who is committed to a facility with a view towards helping them mentally or physically.
The facility where the <fen>Patient</fen> is taken for treatment.

The <fen>Authority</fen> is the actor carrying out the institutionalization with proper legal authorization, either invested into them in general by the government or granted due to power of attorney over the <fen>Patient</fen>.
The time interval during which the institutionalization happens.
The location in which the <fen>Facility</fen> is situated.
The person or persons to whom the <fen>Speaker</fen> delivers their text.
The person who orally delivers a text about a <fen>Topic</fen> to a passive <fen>Audience</fen>.
What the text that the <fen>Speaker</fen> produces is about.
The <fen>Time</fen> describes when the speaking occurs.
The <fen>Place</fen> describes the location where the speaking occurs.
<fen>Theme</fen> is the object that moves. It may be an entity that moves under its own power, but it need not be.
<fen>Goal</fen> is any expression that tells where the <fen>Theme</fen> ends up, or would end up, as a result of the motion.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when arriving occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the arriving event occurs.
